i'm a private citizen and not looking to make any political decisions this year,'' she said thursday after her election to the board. feinstein said the job with the san francisco-based bank is ``an opportunity for me to learn more about a major business in the bay area and the state of california.''
the bancal holding company, which does business in california, oregon and washington, has approximately $4 billion in assets
the board was expanded from 15 to 16 members to make room for the ex-mayor, who attended her first meeting after her election and was assigned to the trust committee. trust operations account for 30 percent of the bank's business
i'm just a beginner,'' she said later. ``i'm learning.''
