the russians are willing to (talk) but secretly. they are trying for it but secretly, not openly,'' hekmatyar said
hekmatyar also said that only an agreement with the resistance would guarantee the red army's safe passage out of afghanistan
the guerrillas do not recognize kabul's soviet-backed government and have said the u.n. talks are useless because they don't directly involve them and the soviets
the russians have to realize the fact that without an agreement with the mujahedeen it is not possible for the afghan crisis to be solved,'' said hekmatyar
he said the guerrillas would stop fighting if the soviet troops withdraw unconditionally and abandon attempts to preserve the communists' power
we will give them safe passage to leave afghanistan ... if they take the government they brought by their forces along with them,'' hekmatyar said. ``we will open the gates of afghanistan for them to leave.''
