mustafa arafat was among the first to join his brother's fatah guerrilla group, the largest of eight factions in the plo, nearly 25 years ago
the plo chairman is known to have two living brothers _ fat'hy, the hospital director, and gamal, who represents the plo in north yemen _ and a sister in cairo who is known by the code-name um al-mumeneen, ``mother of the faithful.''
police have charged the owner of two dogs with criminally negligent homicide after the dogs chased a bicyclist who fell and died
candelario guerrero, 45, was released from the williamson county jail on thursday after posting $1,500 bond on the misdemeanor charge, which carries penalties of up to a year in jail and a $2,000 fine
donald carlyle westbrook, 41, of austin, who rode his bicycle 30 to 40 miles each day, died from head injuries, according to police officer bryan leath
westbrook was riding near guerrero's business tuesday when two dogs started to chase him, according to the police report. as he sped up to flee the dogs, westbrook looked back, lost control of his bicycle and flipped over the handlebars, the report said
he died wednesday. his heart was transplanted into an austin woman thursday morning, and one of his kidneys was transplanted into another patient
the dogs, police said, were used to guard guerrero's automotive repair business. guerrero was at the business when the dogs got out through an open gate, leath said
