these are another expression of the arab refusal to accept israel, to coexist with us, and to recognize that israel is a permanent feature in the region,'' shamir said
the protesters ``cry, `palestine is arab,' and openly declare that all of palestine is theirs,'' shamir told about 1,500 members of the jewish community at a dedication of a cornerstone for a museum commemorating the holocaust
these are not passive civil rights marches,'' he said
shamir, fresh from his meeting with president reagan, secretary of state george p. shultz and congressional leaders, reiterated his opposition to an american plan for peace in the middle east that calls for an international conference
shamir, his address punctuated by enthusiastic applause, said the proposal would play into the hands of the soviets and arabs, who he said are trying to bypass direct talks with israel
we are for direct negotiations, without preconditions, for open talks at which each side will present its views and claims on an equal footing, without outside intervention,'' shamir said
he called on his audience to close ranks behind israel as it tries to quell rioting by palestinians on the west bank and the gaza strip, which israel has occupied since the 1967 mideast war
when unity breaks down, then our enemies exploit every critical statement to their own end,'' he said, referring apparently to criticism by some american jews of the israeli army's use of beatings and live ammunition to quell the riots
at least 100 palestinians have been killed in more than three months of violence, and hundreds wounded
