large-capital industrials, steels and electricals fared well during the day, but construction issues were weak, possibly due to friction with the united states, according to a dealer who asked that he not be further identified
the nikkei index has been gaining for the past four days, and today's closing figure was the highest recorded since stock prices plunged last october
the trade figures were better than we had expected, and we're seeing a strengthening of bullish sentiment'' said a broker with a major firm who also spoke on condition of anonymity
according to figures released by the u.s. department of commerce thursday, the u.s. trade deficit with japan for january was $3.95 billion, down from $4.79 billion in december. the total trade deficit for january was $12.44 billion, up from $12.20 billion the month before
here is a list of the 10 largest commercial bank collapses in the united states, ranked by asset size, according to the federal deposit insurance corp
1. continental illinois corp., chicago; assisted by fdic july 26, 1984; $33.6 billion assets; $4.5 billion fdic outlay; $1.7 billion expected cost to fdic
2. first republicbank corp., dallas; assisted march 17, 1988; $33.2 billion assets; $1 billion outlay; unknown expected cost
3. first city bancorporation, houston; assisted sept. 9, 1987; $12.2 billion assets; $970 million outlay; $800 million-$900 million expected cost. (the rescue package is contingent on approval by march 29, 1988 from the bank's debt holders
4. first pennsylvania bank, philadelphia; assisted april 28, 1980; $5.5 billion assets; $325 million outlay, since repaid; zero cost
5. franklin national bank, new york; failed oct. 8, 1974; $3.6 billion assets; $1.8 billion outlay, since repaid; zero cost
6. first national bank &amp; trust co. of oklahoma city; failed july 14, 1986; $1.4 billion assets; $635 million outlay; $347 million expected cost
7. first national bank of midland, texas; failed oct. 14, 1983; $1.4 billion assets; $1.2 billion outlay; $615 million cost
8. banctexas group inc., dallas; assisted july 17, 1987; $1.3 billion assets; $150 million outlay; $150 million expected cost
9. u.s. national bank, san diego; failed oct. 18, 1983; $1.3 billion assets; $222 million outlay; $67 million cost
10. alaska mutual bank and united bank alaska, anchorage; assisted jan. 28, 1988; $1.3 billion assets; $295 million outlay; unknown expected cost
wealthy entertainer merv griffin, who late last year entered the hotel business by paying $100 million for the beverly hilton in beverly hills, has offered $35 per share, or $225 million, for resorts international inc
but an attorney for new york real estate investor donald trump, who controls about 90 percent of resorts' voting power and is offering $22 per share to take the company private, spurned the thursday offer as ``illusory'' and a ``blatant attempt at market manipulation.''
trump is chairman of resorts international, which operates hotel-casinos in new jersey and the bahamas
griffin's offer, made by his privately owned griffin co. investment concern, is contingent on several conditions, including a provision that trump agree to vote his shres in favor of the merger and agree to terminate his five-year management agreement for resorts' atlantic city properties
trump has ``no intention of agreeing'' to those conditions, said his attorney, jack nusbaum
in light of the stance by trump, resorts' board decided at a thursday meeting that griffin's offer was ``moot.'' therefore, the board decided not to withdraw its recommendation in favor of trump's $22-per-share offer
in response, griffin spokesman mark gill said griffin is considering legal action against resorts' outside directors for breach of fiduciary duty to shareholders other than trump. three of resorts' six directors are trump nominees
despite insistence by trump that he would not raise his offer, resorts stock closed thursday at $25.25 per share, up $3.37{
griffin said it decided to make the offer after talks with f.v. scutti, a major holder of resorts' class a common stock who is dissatisfied with trump's offer. scutti owns about 5 percent of the htel-casino company
resorts has 5.7 million class a shares outstanding, each of which is entitled to one vote. it also has 752,000 class b shares, nearly all of which are owned by trump and each of which has 100 votes
in atlantic city, n.j., resorts, which maintains corporate offices in both atlantic city and north miami, fla., owns the 700-room resorts casino hotel and undeveloped real estate facing the boardwalk and is building the 42-floor, 1,250-room taj mahal
it also operates a casino and owns and operates hotel facilities with 1,370 rooms on paradise island in the bahamas
work on the luxurious and expensive taj mahal, which will be the largest hotel-casino in new jersey when it is completed, has been at the root of financial problems for resorts
trump bought control of resorts when its stock was depressed by those difficulties, and he was granted the five-year operating agreement of resorts' atlantic city properties in exchange for agreeing to help raise financing to complete the taj mahal
that financing hasn't yet been arranged, and trump has offered $22 per share to buy out other shareholders and take the company private. initially, trump had offered $15 per share, but a number of class a shareholders sued and trump raised his offer to settle those suits. a court hearing to approve those settlements is scheduled for friday in delaware, where resorts is based
nusbaum contended the offer by griffin was arranged by scutti in an effort to force trump to raise his bid again
besides the beverly hilton, the griffin co. owns several radio stations and the nation's largest supplier of closed-circuit tv systems, which are widely used at facilities such as racetracks. it also has extensive real estate holdings in beverly hills and northern california
merv griffin is a 10-time emmy award winner who served for 23 years as host of ``the merv griffin show,'' one of tv's longest-running programs
