gainers among the blue chips included ford motor, up [ at 44}; coca-cola, up [ at 40[, and exxon, up ] at 44]. but international business machines dropped | to 114\ and american express lost | to 26]
the nyse's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose .27 to 152.95. at the american stock exchange, the market value index was up .35 at 299.34
on thursday the dow jones industrial average rose 21.72 points to 2,086.04, the highest level since the oct. 19 crash
advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 9 to 5 on the nyse, with 995 up, 554 down and 442 unchanged. big board volume totaled 211.92 million shares, against 153.59 million the previous session
pillsbury co.'s stock headed lower today after a two-day run-up, apparently dampened by a report of a larger-than-expected quarterly loss and word that the company was negotiating to sell its godfather's pizza chain
rumors that the food and restaurant giant is a takeover target pushed pillsbury's stock up more than $7 a share over the course of two days. on thursday, pillsbury closed at $45.37{ in heavy new york stock exchange trading
but that trend reversed today, when the stock fell 25 cents a share to $45.12{
pillsbury said thursday it lost $107.8 million during the third fiscal quarter, $50 million more than anticipated and a sharp downturn from the $48.5 million, or 56-cents-a-share profit posted in the year-ago period
sales during the quarter fell to $1.5 billion from $1.53 billion a year earlier
william spoor, pillsbury chairman and chief executive, acknowledged in a letter to shareholders, ``given our many recent disappointments, it is not surprising that we have raised investor skepticism and questions about our future.''
but he said he remained committed to keeping the company independent. ``now we must demonstrate, through action and not words, that we can perform at levels commensurate with our potential,'' he said
spoor said the quarterly loss, which stemmed from $140.9 million in restructuring charges to close businesses, restaurant properties and plants, would contribute to an earnings decline in fiscal 1988, which ends may 31
two-thirds of the charges occurred in the company's restaurant division
the 580-unit godfather's chain, which pillsbury acquired in 1985, was put on the block because it did not have near-term potential to be ``a major strategic component of pillsbury's portfolio,'' spoor stated
company spokesman johnny thompson said negotiations were under way with the management team of omaha, neb.-based godfather's, but he declined to comment on whether pillsbury had received any offers
pillsbury earlier announced plans to sell its bay street, key west grill and quik wok restaurant chains. spoor said the company had received a letter of intent from an unidentified party to buy bay street
however, spoor reiterated that burger king, the company's biggest restaurant operation, is not for sale
analysts had been expecting pillsbury to announce a restructuring _ including the sale of its steak &amp; ale, bennigan's and godfather's restaurant operations _ ever since chairman john stafford resigned last month and spoor took over as interim chairman
pillsbury's announcement in february of lower-than-expected earnings for the fiscal year ended in may preceded stafford's feb. 29 departure
analysts have speculated that potential buyers for pillsbury could include swiss-based nestle sa, beatrice co. of chicago and new york investor saul steinberg
stock prices pushed ahead today, extending the advance that has carried the market to its highest levels since black monday last fall
the dow jones average of 30 industrials rose 9.95 to 2,095.99 by 11 a.m. on wall street
